<item>
            <title>[FLINK-11779] CLI ignores -m parameter if high-availability is ZOOKEEPER </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11779</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Description&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The CLI will ignores the host/port provided by the &lt;tt&gt;-m&lt;/tt&gt; parameter if &lt;tt&gt;high-availability: ZOOKEEPER&lt;/tt&gt; is configured in &lt;tt&gt;flink-conf.yaml&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected behavior&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;TBD: either document this behavior or give precedence to &lt;tt&gt;-m&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
